race.comment: SURFY PETE (2) was returning from a break last time out and proved too classy, scoring by 2 lengths over 1300m at Mortlake. Fitter for that last hitout and is the testing material. KENTAHTEN (1) has only won one of 30 starts but is rarely far away and goes particularly well second-up with four top-three finishes from five runs. Gets the draw and rider to suggest he'll be around the mark again. ZAMORA (3) finished out of the money two starts back then was beaten 2.75 lengths when fourth over 1200m at Ballarat a week-and-a-half ago after being prominent at the corner. Likely improver with strong prospects. LIBERTY RAE (10) can improve now third-up into the campaign.
